article.headline: Wagner 57, St. Francis, Pa., 54
article.story: LORETTO, Pa. (AP) -- Joey Mundweiler and Justin Drummond each scored 10 points as Wagner raced to a double-digit lead and held on to beat St. Francis, Pa., 57-54 Saturday night. Wagner (10-15, 7-7 Northeast Conference) built a 17-point lead in the first half, but needed to hold off a frantic rally in the final minute for the win. Jelani Lawrence and Cale Nelson each had 14 points for St. Francis (5-21, 2-13). Devin Sweetney added 12 points. The Seahawks led 56-51 with 46 seconds left before the Red Flash scored three quick points. Wagner's Jamal Smith hit one of two free throws with 13.4 seconds remaining to make it 57-54. St. Francis had a chance to tie at the buzzer, but Marquis Ford misfired on a 3-point attempt. Wagner scored the first seven points of the game and led 28-11 with 5:59 to go in the first half. The Red Flash trailed 50-36 with 7:54 left, before battling back into contention.
